<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Perfect hotel for a relaxing weekend My wife and I have just returned from a 3-day trip to Barcelona, and couldn't rate the H1898 highly enough. We have been to Barcelona several times before but this was our first trip to this hotel -- we won't be staying anywhere else in future as you won't find a better hotel for the price.The best bits:* The roof terrace -- very stylishly put together, with sun loungers, a bar, a (small) pool and lots of other seating, including two large double-bed sized mattresses perfect for soaking up the sun on* The pool in the spa in the basement. A superb setting in a converted cellar, with free use also of the gym, steam room and sauna - a relaxing way to end the trip and grab a shower before jumping on the plane if you have an evening flight* It's a brand new hotel, so everything is pristine -- no lumpy pillows or bashed light fittings here* The location -- right on Las Ramblas, but very few rooms actually overlook the road so is isn't noisy. It's situated near the top of the Ramblas opposite Le Meridien -- 5 mins from Plaza Catalunya, the metro system, El Corte Ingles and the airport bus stopWhat types of people you'll see there:* Couples in their mid 30s-mid 50s* Well-heeled groups of twentysomethings* Business peopleWe booked a corner room (if you're booking online it's the room with red furnishings rather than black) which was a little bigger than a standard room and becaise it was on a corner had an extra window. Would probably book a standard room next time, although judging by the relative size of the rooms on the fire exit plan they look fairly compact.We didn't try room service (there are too many good tapas bars around) -- the only thing we'd change is to provide coffee and tea-making facilities in the room. Tea is complementary, but you need to call down for hot water.In case you're hungry there are loads of good tapas bars around, and the restaurant on the 1st floor of the building opposite the hotel on Las Ramblas 