<Content>Quiet, clean hotel, centrally located I spent 5 nights here at the end of June/early July, in a superior room without breakfast included. The room was large and looked out on what appeared to be an alleyway. I believe there was some sort of small restaurant with a patio there, and there was occasional noise as a result. However, it was generally very quiet, and I'm not especially worried about the view. The furnishings and decor are contemporary, though the materials used seem fairly simple.There was a very comfortable king-size bed with nice linens and various pillows to choose from. To their credit, hotel management has installed hardwood floors in the entryway and main room. Air conditioning was excellent and the closet was large. There was a flat-panel wall-mounted LCD TV. The lighting, in its various settings, can be controlled from the bed.The bathroom is nicely done in green stone and was very roomy. Huge towels, constantly replenished toiletries (including toothbrush/toothpaste, razor/shaving cream, and the usual other supplies), plush bathrobes and disposable slippers were provided. The showerhead is about the size of a dinner plate and water pressure and temperature were excellent.There is a restaurant which is really not too bad. I had dinner a couple of times and found the staff to be very pleasant and helpful. The food, while not wildly creative (go to Abac, Moo, Cinc Sentits, Comer莽 24, etc. for that), was tasty and featured good ingredients and simple preparations.I didn't spend a great deal of time interacting with the staff or using the spa. The lobby area is somewhat dark but tastefully decorated. Features of the old Compa帽铆a General de Tabacos de Filipinas building have been carefully preserved.I would recommend this hotel to my friends and colleagues. The client猫le wasn't upper crust (if that matters to you), and there seemed to be a number of small tour groups booked in as well. I only hope that the current standard of the hotel will be